concept_set_name: [HCUP] RSP016 Other specified and unspecified lower respiratory disease
concept_set_version_title: [HCUP] RSP016 Other specified and unspecified lower respiratory disease (v1)
comments: Exported from VSAC and bulk imported to N3C.
intention: ICD-10-CM Body System (largely aligned with ICD-10-CM chapters) diseases of the respiratory system. RSP contains 17 categories that include diseases of the respiratory system such a as influenza, asthma, acute bronchitis, and pneumothorax.
limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD-10-CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems.  For more information about the CCSR: https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/toolssoftware/ccsr/DXCCSR-User-Guide-v2022-1.pdf
provenance: AHRQ National Inpatient Sample, Healthcare Cost & Utilization Project (HCUP), 2019

concept_set_version_title: [HCUP] BLD007 Diseases of white blood cells (v1)
comments: Exported from VSAC and bulk imported to N3C.
intention: ICD-10-CM Body System (largely aligned with ICD-10-CM chapters) diseases of the blood and blood-forming organs and certain disorders involving the immune mechanism. BLD contains 10 categories that include diseases related to the blood, diseases of blood-forming organs, and certain disorders involving the immune mechanism such as nutritional anemia, sickle cell/trait anemia, and immunity disorders.
limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD-10-CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems. intention: ICD-10-CM Body System (largely aligned with ICD-10-CM chapters) diseases of the circulatory system. CIR contains 39 categories that include diseases of the circulatory system such as essential hypertension, acute myocardial infarction, heart failure, and cerebral infarction.
limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD-10-CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems.  For more information about the CCSR: https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/toolssoftware/ccsr/DXCCSR-User-Guide-v2022-1.pdf
provenance: AHRQ National Inpatient Sample, Healthcare Cost & Utilization Project (HCUP), 2019

intention: ICD-10-CM Body System (largely aligned with ICD-10-CM chapters) diseases of the circulatory system. CIR contains 39 categories that include diseases of the circulatory system such as essential hypertension, acute myocardial infarction, heart failure, and cerebral infarction.
limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD-10-CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems.  For more information about the CCSR: https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/toolssoftware/ccsr/DXCCSR-User-Guide-v2022-1.pdf
provenance: AHRQ National Inpatient Sample, Healthcare Cost & Utilization Project (HCUP), 2019

comments: Exported from VSAC and bulk imported to N3C.
intention: ICD-10-CM Body System (largely aligned with ICD-10-CM chapters) diseases of the digestive system. DIG contains 25 categories that include diseases of the digestive system such as appendicitis and other appendiceal conditions, hepatic failure, diverticulosis and diverticulitis, and intestinal infection.
limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD-10-CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems.  For more information about the CCSR: https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/toolssoftware/ccsr/DXCCSR-User-Guide-v2022-1.pdf
provenance: AHRQ National Inpatient Sample, Healthcare Cost & Utilization Project (HCUP), 2019

intention: ICD-10-CM Body System (largely aligned with ICD-10-CM chapters) diseases of the digestive system. DIG contains 25 categories that include diseases of the digestive system such as appendicitis and other appendiceal conditions, hepatic failure, diverticulosis and diverticulitis, and intestinal infection.
limitations: The grouping is based on Clinical Classifications Software Refines (CCSR). The CCSR for ICD-10-CM provides a method for aggregating the diagnosis codes into over 530 clinical categories across 21 body systems.  For more information about the CCSR: https://www.hcup-us.ahrq.gov/toolssoftware/ccsr/DXCCSR-User-Guide-v2022-1.pdf
provenance: AHRQ National Inpatient Sample, Healthcare Cost & Utilization Project (HCUP), 2019
